===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A slick and light [[ship]] for making pleasure trips or racing on water, having sails but often motor-powered. At times used as a residence offshore on a dock.
#: {{ux|en|Would you like to go sailing on my uncle’s '''yacht'''?}}
#: {{ux|en|You are a true yachtsman! Are you a member of the local '''yacht''' club?}}
#* {{RQ:Churchill Celebrity|chapter=10|passage=The skipper Mr. Cooke had hired at Far Harbor was a God-fearing man with a luke warm interest in his new billet and employer, and had only been prevailed upon to take charge of the '''yacht''' after the offer of an emolument equal to half a year's sea pay of an ensign in the navy.}}
# Any vessel used for private, noncommercial purposes.
#* {{RQ:Chambers Younger Set|VI|passage=“I don’t mean all of your friends—only a small proportion—which, however, connects your circle with that deadly, idle, brainless bunch—the insolent chatterers at the opera,{{nb...}}, the chlorotic squatters on huge '''yachts''',{{nb...}}, the neurotic victims of mental cirrhosis, the jewelled animals whose moral code is the code of the barnyard—!"}}
